title: Cloak golden gate — cloak handling and the brass hook
story: cloak-of-darkness
description: Wearing, removing, hanging (custom verb), taking, and alias
  resolution for the cloak and hook per cloak.story. The `hang` verb is
  `define verb hang or hook means put (something) on (something)`.
  ADR-210 AC-1 golden gate (frozen 2026-07-10).

---

# The player starts wearing the cloak
> examine cloak
[OK: contains "handsome cloak, of velvet trimmed with satin"]

# Into the Cloakroom
> west
[OK: contains "Cloakroom"]

> examine hook
[OK: contains "small brass hook, screwed to the wall"]

# Remove the cloak, then hang it with the story-defined verb
> remove cloak
[OK: contains "take off the velvet cloak"]

> hang cloak on hook
[OK: contains "put the velvet cloak on the brass hook"]

# Take it back — and exercise the hook's "peg" alias with the canonical form
> take cloak
[OK: contains "Taken"]

> put cloak on peg
[OK: contains "put the velvet cloak on the brass hook"]

# Retrieve and wear again
> take cloak
[OK: contains "Taken"]

> wear cloak
[OK: contains "put on the velvet cloak"]
